4-14:We hypothesize that WIG is positively correlated with retrieval effectiveness because high quality retrieval should be much more effective than just returning the average document .
4-15:The heart of this technique is how to estimate the joint distribution P(Qs,Dt) .
4-16:In the language modeling approach to IR, a variety of models can be applied readily to estimate this distribution .
4-17:Although most of these models are based on the bagof words assumption, recent work on modeling term dependence under the language modeling framework have shown consistent and significant improvements in retrieval effectiveness over bagof words models .
4-18:Inspired by the success of incorporating term proximity features into language models, we decide to adopt a good dependence model to estimate the probability P(Qs,Dt) .
4-19:The model we chose for this paper is Metzler and Croft"s Markov Random Field model, which has already demonstrated superiority over a number of collections and different retrieval tasks [8,9] .
