4-95:3.3 First Rank Change In this section, we propose a method called the first rank change for performance prediction for NP queries .
4-96:This method is derived from the ranking robustness technique [1] that is mainly designed for content based queries .
4-97:When directly applied to NP queries, the robustness technique will be less effective because it takes the top ranked documents as a whole into account while NP queries usually have only one single relevant document .
4-98:Instead, our technique focuses on the first rank document while the main idea of the robustness method remains .
4-99:Specifically, the pseudocode for computing FRC is shown in figure 1 .
4-100:Input: (1) ranked list L={Di} where i=1,100 .
4-101:Di denotes the i th ranked document .
