5-21:We make use of the Markov Random field model for both ad hoc and Named Page finding retrieval .
5-22:We adopt the same setting of retrieval parameters used in [8,9] .
5-23:The Indri search engine [12] is used for all of our experiments .
5-24:Though not reported here, we also tried the query likelihood model for ad hoc retrieval and found that the results change little because of the very high correlation between the query performances obtained by the two retrieval models (0.96 measured by Pearson"s coefficient) .
5-25:4.2 Known Query Types Suppose that query types are known .
5-26:We treat each type of query separately and measure the correlation with average precision (or the reciprocal rank in the case of NP queries) .
5-27:We adopt the Pearson"s correlation test which reflects the degree of linear relationship between the predicted and the actual retrieval performance .
